        <tr>
          <td>
            <table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="2">
              <tr> 
                <td class="chblue"><font class="h1font"> Fun Decks</font></td></tr></table></td></tr><tr><td><table width="100%" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="3"><tr><td><font class="bfont"><table width="100%" border="0" cellpadding="4" cellspacing="0"><tr><td colspan="2"><font class="h1font">We want... a shrubbery!</font></td></tr><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Rating</Font></TD><TD><table width='98' border='0' cellspacing='0' cellpadding='0'><tr><td background='/magination/gfx/5star.gif'><img src='/lotr/gfx/trans.gif' width='1' height='25'></td></tr></table><font size=1>(4.91)</font> | <A HREF="/magination/decks/decks.php?reviews=23619">Read Reviews</A></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Author</font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> <A HREF="http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=10207">Douglas "Shen" Camp</A></FONT> <font class="afont"> <a href='http://www.decktech.net/magination/main/mpage.php?member=10207&sub=1'> (Subscribe to this member)</a></font></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Description</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> Another Monty Python and the Holy Grail inspired theme deck. Uses the Paradwyn (the shrubbery of the deck) and Bograth (The Knights Who Say... Ni! of the deck) regions. If done right you&#8217;ll drive your opponent crazy; you&#8217;ll see why later. Also</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Submitted</Font></TD><TD><font class="bfont"> May 27, 2002</FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Cards</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> <b>Word of warning:</b> I&#8217;ve had problems developing a deck that revolves around the line, &#8220;We want&#8230; a shrubbery!&#8221; Thankfully though, I was able to get all of the cards to fit into the theme of the deck without too much trouble. Just keep in mind all Paradwyn related cards represent the shrubbery that the &#8220;Knights who say Ni&#8221; were asking for. Also keep in mind the &#8220;Knights who say Ni&#8221; said they required a sacrifice, thus you&#8217;ll find quite a few critters that can be popped (sacrificed) for some sort of effect.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Disclaimer:</b> Again, this is a deck that doesn&#8217;t follow the formula I normally use. I would also ask that you remember this is a Fun deck. As such, I hope to be rated on the presentation of this deck (Aaaaugh!), the goodies I&#8217;ve included, and the shear hilarity you&#8217;ll have playing this deck against your opponents. However, you might find that due to the nature of the deck, it (Aaaaugh!) could cause your friends to refuse to play against this deck ever again. You&#8217;ll see what I mean. Finally, this deck wasn&#8217;t really built to win, but if it (Aaaaugh!) happened to do so that will just be icing on the cake.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Magi:</b><br />
<b><I>Golthub</I></b><br />
<I>Reason(s) for using as 1st magi:</I> First off, he&#8217;ll be able to start with two-thirds of his starting cards. Next his power of <b>Mire</b> in my opinion simulates the pain caused when the Knights who say Ni said the word &#8220;Ni&#8221;. Well sort of. So when/if you use Golthub&#8217;s Mire ability you should say, &#8220;Ni!&#8221; Another reason for using Golthub is due to the fact that in his flavor text the word &#8220;it&#8221; shows up. As soon as you <a href="javascript:card_browser(562)">Turn</a> over Golthub you should say, &#8220;Aaaaugh&#8221; due to the word &#8220;it&#8221; being printed on Golthub&#8217;s card. Finally, strategically you&#8217;ll be able to draw three random cards at the beginning and have the constant threat of his Mire ability to possibly slow your opponent down.<br />
<I>Starting Cards:</I> Gremble, Moob, and three random starting cards.<br />
<br />
<b><I>Eryss</I></b><br />
<I>Reason(s) for using as 2nd magi:</I> Her ability of Discordia is another ability you can say Ni every time you use it. She also happens to be both a Paradwyn and Bograth magi. Another plus for using her is the fact she will be able to pull four cards from your discard/draw pile when she is <a href="javascript:card_browser(562)">Turn</a>ed over. Finally, in her flavor text the word &#8220;it&#8221; shows up. That means when you <a href="javascript:card_browser(562)">Turn</a> her over you should say, &#8220;Aaaaugh!&#8221;<br />
<I>Starting Cards:</I> Fog Hyren, Gremble, N&#8217;kala, and Poison <a href="javascript:card_browser(501)">Baloo Root</a>.<br />
<br />
<b><I>Blygt</I></b><br />
<I>Reason(s) for using as 3rd magi:</I> Personally I feel Blygt&#8217;s hat/cowl makes him the perfect Head Knight of the Knights who say Ni for this deck. Yes, I know Gorran&#8217;s hat would in fact make him the perfect Head Knight of the Knights who say Ni for Bograth in general. However, that wasn&#8217;t enough. Gorran didn&#8217;t start with any of the cards that will be used in this deck, and in <a href="javascript:card_browser(562)">Turn</a> his abilities wouldn&#8217;t work with this deck. As it (Aaaaugh!) is, Blygt&#8217;s ability and starting cards will work well with this deck. Also keep in mind that every time Blygt uses his ability you should say, &#8220;Ni!&#8221; since his ability is one of the most annoying in Magi-Nation to date.<br />
<I>Starting Cards:</I> Moob and Moss Quido.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Creatures (32):</b><br />
2 Fog Hyren<br />
2 Gremble<br />
3 Moob<br />
3 Moss Quido<br />
2 Muck <a href="javascript:card_browser(408)">Vinoc</a><br />
3 Mydra<br />
3 N&#8217;Kala<br />
3 Poison <a href="javascript:card_browser(501)">Baloo Root</a><br />
3 Quido Swarm<br />
3 Taglat<br />
3 Treeph<br />
2 Trulb<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Spells (8):</b><br />
2 Crushing Darkness<br />
2 Darkness<br />
2 Spirit Drain<br />
2 Trulb Horde<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Relics (4):</b><br />
1 Dead Wood Staff<br />
1 Great Throne Mushrooms<br />
1 Moss Pendant<br />
1 Rayje&#8217;s Shield<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Total:</b> 42 cards + 3 magi<br />
   </FONT></TD></TR><TR><TD WIDTH="10%" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="h2font"> Strategy</Font></TD><TD> </TD></TR><TR><TD COLSPAN="2" VALIGN="TOP"><font class="bfont"> <br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Errata:</b> In the disclaimer I accidentally put a &#8220;(Aaaaugh!)&#8221; right before the word &#8220;deck&#8221;. I also misrepresented the total number of cards as 42 + 3 magi. There are in fact 44 cards + 3 magi. I&#8217;m only using this many cards since I have quite a bit of drawing power.<br />
<br />
<br />
Well its (Aaaaugh!) time for me to explain the card choices. Thankfully, unlike the <b>Holy Hand Grenade</b> deck, I won&#8217;t have to go into a huge amount of detail with each card. Matter of fact I&#8217;m going to simply make some lists as to what area(s) a card belongs to. For instance, there will be a list of cards with the word &#8220;it&#8221; printed on the card. There still will be a card I&#8217;ll have to explain separately from the rest, but that won&#8217;t be till the end of the formal strategy section and right before the Monty Python scenes. Remember, to get the full enjoyment out of this deck and so you drive your friends and opponents crazy you need to say the words &#8220;Ni&#8221; and &#8220;Aaaaugh!&#8221; at the times I&#8217;ve indicated below.<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Cards you should say, &#8220;Ni&#8221; when you use an ability printed on them or play them.</b><br />
Golthub <I>(Magi)</I><br />
Eryss <I>(Magi)</I><br />
Blygt <I>(Magi)</I><br />
Muck Vinoc <I>(Bograth creature)</I><br />
Poison Baloo Root <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Taglat <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Treepsh <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Crushing Stench <I>(Bograth spell)</I><br />
Darkness <I>(Bograth spell)</I><br />
Spirit Drain <I>(Bograth spell)</I><br />
Great Throne Mushrooms <I>(Bograth Relic)</I><br />
Moss Pendant <I>(Bograth Relic)</I><br />
Rayje&#8217;s Shield <I>(Promo Universal Relic)</I><br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Cards you should say &#8220;Aaaaugh!&#8221; when you play them due to the word &#8220;it&#8221; being printed on the card.</b><br />
Golthub <I>(Magi)</I><br />
Eryss <I>(Magi)</I><br />
Mydra <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
N&#8217;Kala <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Poison Baloo Root <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Quido Swarm <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Taglat <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Trulb <I>(Bograth creature)</I><br />
Trulb Horde <I>(Bograth spell)</I><br />
Deadwood Staff <I>(Bograth Relic)</I><br />
Great Throne Mushrooms <I>(Bograth Relic)</I><br />
Moss Pendant <I>(Bograth Relic)</I><br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Cards that represent the shrubbery of the deck. You could say, &#8220;We want... a shrubbery!&#8221; when you play one of these cards. You&#8217;ll notice there are cards listed here that you could say, &#8220;Ni!&#8221; or &#8220;Aaaaugh!&#8221; as you play them. It might be a good idea to change to &#8220;We want... a shrubbery!&#8221; every now and then for flavor.</b><br />
Fog Hyren <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Gremble <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Mydra <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
N&#8217;Kala <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Poison Baloo Root <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Quido Swarm <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Taglat <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
Treepsh <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Cards that represent the sacrifice asked for by the Head Knight of the &#8220;Knights Who Say Ni!&#8221; You might also might consider saying, &#8220;We demand a sacrifice!&#8221; every time you use one of these cards&#8217; abilities.</b><br />
Gremble <I>(Paradwyn/Bograth creature)</I><br />
