<b>Cards that work with most of the sacrifice cards of the deck.</b><br />
Great Throne Mushrooms <I>(Bograth Relic)</I><br />
Rayje&#8217;s Shield <I>(Promo Universal Relic)</I><br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Further explanation of Rayje&#8217;s Shield.</b><br />
<b><I>Rayje&#8217;s Shield:</I></b> Every knight has to have a standard and that standard usually was represented on his shield. Thus, Rayje&#8217;s Shield is being used as the Knights Who Say Ni standard for this deck. Also, for those of you who haven&#8217;t seen this card, Rayje&#8217;s Shield was a promo card that was handed out at the last storyline tournament. Basically it allows you to place one energy on a creature every time you draw a card. This ability cannot be used on the same creature twice during the same turn.<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
Well I hope you&#8217;ve enjoyed reading everything so far. I also hope I&#8217;ve made it clear how fun this deck will be to play against your friends and other opponents. Now that I&#8217;ve finally finished the write up for this deck, I might even take this deck to a tournament just to annoy all my opponents. I can just see everyone&#8217;s reaction when I started saying &#8220;Ni&#8221; or &#8220;Aaaaugh!&#8221; as I played all the cards. It (Aaaaugh!) would be even funnier if I got others saying &#8220;Ni&#8221; or &#8220;Aaaaugh!&#8221; along with me as I played the game. :P<br />
<br />
As for combos, I know most decks that have been posted have at least a small section of combos listed. I just felt it would be best to list why the cards are included to increase the fun factor of the deck instead of taking the time to figure out a ton of combos this deck could pull off. I will however make the same offer I did when David and I posted the Holy Hand Grenade deck; if you figure out a combo and I like it, I&#8217;ll post the combo and give you the credit for the combo, even if it is a well known combo. <br />
<br />
I would also ask that if you do decide to rate this deck lower than five stars to let me know exactly where I failed to make this deck the type you would definitely play for fun. I ask this so that I can continue to improve the presentation and richness of the Fun decks I post. After all, do you really want to continue seeing what you consider less than perfect five star rated Fun decks posted by me?<br />
<br />
Anyhow as promised the rest of this strategy section contains the famous Knights Who Say Ni scenes from Monty Python and the Holy Grail. You&#8217;ll also find a web site listing that will allow you to get even more wacky Monty Python material. Till next time, don&#8217;t let the French hit you with any flying cows. Hmm. I wonder if I can make a deck revolving around the flying cow scene(s) of Monty Python and the Holy Grail?<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Scene 13 from Monty Python and the Holy Grail:</b><br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Ni! Ni! Ni! Ni! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Who are you? <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> We are the Knights Who Say... Ni! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> No! Not the Knights Who Say Ni! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> The same! <br />
<br />
<b><I>BEDEVERE:</I></b> Who are they? <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> We are the keepers of the sacred words: Ni, Ping, and Nuu-wom! <br />
<br />
<b><I>RANDOM:</I></b> Nuu-wom! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Those who hear them seldom live to tell the tale! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> The Knights Who Say Ni demand a sacrifice! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Knights of Ni, we are but simple travellers who seek the enchanter who lives beyond these woods. <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Ni! Ni! Ni! Ni! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR and PARTY:</I></b> Oh, ow!<br />
 <br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> We shall say &#39;nee&#39; again to you if you do not appease us. <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Well, what is it you want? <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> We want... a shrubbery! <br />
<br />
[dramatic chord] <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> A what? <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Ni! Ni! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR and PARTY:</I></b> Oh, ow! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Please, please! No more! We will find a shrubbery. <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> You must return here with a shrubbery or else you will never pass through this wood alive! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> O Knights of Ni, you are just and fair, and we will return with a shrubbery. <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> One that looks nice. <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Of course. <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> And not too expensive. <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Yes. <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Now... go!<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Scene 19 from Monty Python and the Holy Grail:</b><br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Knights of Ni, we have brought you your shrubbery. May we go now?<br />
 <br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> It is a good shrubbery. I like the laurels particularly. But there is one small problem. <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> What is that? <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> We are now... no longer the Knights Who Say Ni. <br />
<br />
<b><I>RANDOM:</I></b> Ni! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Shh shh. We are now the Knights Who Say Ecky-ecky-ecky-ecky-pikang-zoom-boing-mumble-mumble. <br />
<br />
<b><I>RANDOM:</I></b> Ni! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Therefore, we must give you a test. <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> What is this test, O Knights of-- Knights Who &#39;Til Recently Said Ni? <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Firstly, you must find... another shrubbery! <br />
<br />
[dramatic chord] <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Not another shrubbery! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Then, when you have found the shrubbery, you must place it here beside this shrubbery, only slightly higher so you get a two-level effect with a little path running down the middle. <br />
<br />
<b><I>RANDOM:</I></b> A path! A path! Ni! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Then, when you have found the shrubbery, you must cut down the mightiest tree in the forest... with... a herring! <br />
<br />
[dramatic chord] <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> We shall do no such thing! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Oh, please! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Cut down a tree with a herring? It can&#39;t be done. <br />
<br />
<b><I>KNIGHTS:</I></b> Aaaaugh! Aaaaugh! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Don&#39;t say that word. <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> What word? <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> I cannot tell, suffice to say is one of the words the Knights of Ni cannot hear. <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> How can we not say the word if you don&#39;t tell us what it is? <br />
<br />
<b><I>KNIGHTS:</I></b> Aaaaugh! Aaaaugh! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> What, `is&#39;? <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> No, not `is&#39; -- we couldn&#39;t get vary far in life not saying `is&#39;. <br />
<br />
<b><I>BEDEVERE:</I></b> My liege, it&#39;s Sir Robin! <br />
<br />
<b><I>MINSTREL (singing):</I></b> <br />
Packing it in and packing it up <br />
And sneaking away and buggering off<br />
And chickening out and pissing off home<br />
Yes, bravely he is throwing in the sponge<br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Oh, Robin! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ROBIN:</I></b> My liege! It&#39;s good to see you! <br />
<br />
<b><I>KNIGHTS:</I></b> Aaaaugh! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> He said the word! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Surely you&#39;ve not given up your quest for the Holy Grail? <br />
<br />
<b><I>MINSTREL (singing):</I></b> He is sneaking away and buggering off- <br />
<br />
<b><I>ROBIN:</I></b> Shut up! No, no no-- far from it. <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> He said the word again! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ROBIN:</I></b> I was looking for it. <br />
<br />
<b><I>KNIGHTS:</I></b> Aaaaugh! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ROBIN:</I></b> Uh, here, here in this forest. <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> No, it is far from&#8212;<br />
<br />
<b><I>KNIGHTS:</I></b> Aaaaugh! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Aaaaugh! Stop saying the word! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Oh, stop it! <br />
<br />
<b><I>KNIGHTS:</I></b> Aaaaugh! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Oh! He said it again! <br />
<br />
<b><I>ARTHUR:</I></b> Patsy! <br />
<br />
<b><I>HEAD KNIGHT:</I></b> Wait! I said it! I said it! Ooh! I said it again! <br />
<br />
<b><I>KNIGHTS:</I></b> Aaaaugh!<br />
<br />
<br />
<br />
<b>Side Note:</b> As I was reading over scene 19 I noticed something weird about it (Aaaaugh!). When the Head Knight was giving the instructions for the second test he said the word &#8220;it&#8221;. I wonder if there were any other flubs like that in these two scenes.<br />
